  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know if a shy guy likes me?",
  "response": "It can be tricky to read a shy guy\u2019s signals since they may not express their feelings overtly. However, there are several signs you can look for to determine if he has feelings for you:\n\n1. **Nervousness Around You**: If he seems a bit anxious or fidgety when you're around, it could be a sign he likes you.\n\n2. **Frequent Glances**: If you catch him looking at you but he quickly looks away when you notice, this may indicate interest.\n\n3. **Engaging in Conversation**: If he tries to initiate conversations or seems eager to keep them going, even if he struggles with shyness, it could be a sign.\n\n4. **Body Language**: Observe his body language. Does he lean in when talking to you? Face you directly? These can be signs of attraction.\n\n5. **Compliments**: If he gives you genuine compliments, even if they are shy or understated, take note. \n\n6. **Help and Support**: If he offers to help you or goes out of his way to be supportive, this might indicate he cares about you.\n\n7. **Interest in Your Life**: If he asks questions about your interests, hobbies, or personal life, it shows he wants to know more about you.\n\n8. **Social Engagement**: Pay attention to how he behaves when you\u2019re with a group versus when it\u2019s just the two of you. Shy guys may open up more when it\u2019s more intimate.\n\n9. **Remembering Details**: If he remembers small details about things you've mentioned in previous conversations, it indicates that he\u2019s paying attention.\n\n10. **Touch**: If he finds ways to initiate light, casual physical contact\u2014like a tap on the shoulder\u2014it can be a sign of attraction.\n\n11. **Finding Reasons to Be Around**: If he tries to spend time with you or shows up at events where he knows you'll be, that's a good indicator.\n\nRemember, everyone expresses interest differently. If you're unsure, consider opening a line of communication by chatting with him more and observing how he responds. Good luck!",
